## Refactoring & Removal Discipline
- **Removal is deliverable**: When asked to "remove" or "replace", delete old code, do not wrap.
- **Fix tests, do not preserve them**: Broken tests after removal are expected cost, not signal to add compatibility.
- **No unwanted backward compatibility**: Add compatibility layers only for external consumers or explicit user request.
- **Tests pass ≠ issue complete**: Verify behavior changed, not only tests passing.

## Design Conformance Verification
- **Tests prove consistency, not correctness**: In LLM-generated codebases, passing tests prove internal consistency of assumptions.
- **Real outputs over test fixtures**: Compare against design docs and real pipeline outputs, not only test expectations.
- **"It runs" is not evidence**: Verify output matches spec and downstream consumers use it.

## Review Quality
- **Model diversity required**: All reviews (code, spec, plan) include at least one reviewer from model different than orchestrating session, plus any current-model reviewers.
- **External dispatch**: Claude CLI, Codex, Cursor, Gemini add perspectives beyond built-in peer pairing; include one when available via `dispatch-external-model` skill.
{{- if eq $agent "claude" }}
- **Claude pairing**: Use Opus when orchestrating on Sonnet, Sonnet when orchestrating on Opus; do not use Haiku for review.
- **Dispatch in Claude Code**: Dispatch peer Claude via Agent tool with `model` override; use `dispatch-external-model` skill for external tools.
{{- else }}
- **Dispatch**: Use native agent dispatch when available; consult `dispatch-external-model` skill for CLI-based dispatch.
{{- end }}
